= Scaffold Guide

This game demonstrates the core Dendry/DendryNexus mechanisms. Each section below explains a mechanism and how to customize it.

@menu

- @cards: Card system (is-hand, is-deck, is-card)
- @timers: Timer and cooldown system
- @factions: Faction strength and dissent
- @elections: Election algorithm
- @events_guide: Event system
- @advisors_guide: Advisor system (is-pinned-card)
- @economy: Economic simulation
- @backSpecialScene: Exit guide.

@cards
go-to: menu

= Card System

The main game loop uses a card-hand metaphor. In main.scene.dry:

**is-hand: true** marks a scene as a card hand. Cards are drawn from decks.

**is-deck: true** marks a scene as a deck. Its choices reference tagged cards.

**is-card: true** marks a scene as a drawable card. The **frequency** property controls draw probability. **max-visits** limits how many times it appears.

**max-cards: 3** limits how many cards can be in the hand at once.

@timers
go-to: menu

= Timer System

Cards use cooldown timers so they do not appear every turn. Pattern:

**on-arrival: fundraising_timer = 6; month_actions += 1**

**view-if: fundraising_timer <= 0**

Timers are decremented in post_event.scene.dry each month. The Q.timers array lists all active timer names.

@factions
go-to: menu

= Faction System

The party has internal factions, each with strength and dissent. Defined in Q.factions. Faction strength is normalized to 100% in post_event. Overall dissent is a weighted average.

Cards affect factions via: **left_dissent -= 10; labor_strength += 5**

@elections
go-to: menu

= Election Algorithm

Elections use class-based proportional voting. Q.classes lists demographic groups, Q.parties lists all parties. Each Q.{class}_{party} value represents support.

The algorithm normalizes per-class support, then weights by class population size. See election_algorithm.scene.dry.

@events_guide
go-to: menu

= Event System

Events are cards tagged with **tags: event**. They appear in the post_event scene when their **view-if** condition is met. One-time events use **max-visits: 1**.

Events typically offer 2-4 choices, each with **on-arrival** effects on variables.

@advisors_guide
go-to: menu

= Advisor System

Advisors use **is-pinned-card: true** and **tags: advisor**. They appear as persistent cards in the hand. Each advisor offers unique actions gated by **advisor_action_timer**.

@economy
go-to: menu

= Economic Simulation

Three core variables drive the economy: Q.inflation, Q.unemployed, Q.economic_growth. These interact via feedback loops in post_event.scene.dry (Phillips curve, budget effects).

High unemployment reduces republic support. Inflation and deflation have cascading effects on growth.
